## Shared Requirements (Both Patterns)

### aria-labels on all controls

Every interactive control (prev/next buttons, pagination dots) must have an `aria-label`:

```tsx
<button aria-label="Go to slide 3" />
<button aria-label="Next slide" />
```

### prefers-reduced-motion

Auto-advancing carousels must respect the user's motion preference:

```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const prefersReduced = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;
  if (!prefersReduced) {
    startTimer();
  }
  return stopTimer;
}, []);
```

For CSS transitions on slide changes:

```css
.slide {
  transition: opacity 300ms ease;
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .slide {
    transition: none;
  }
}
```

---

## Choosing the Right Pattern

| Situation | Pattern |
|---|---|
| Product tiles, order history cards, category chips | Pattern 1 — Scroll Snap |
| Hero campaign, full-width promotional banner | Pattern 2 — Auto-Advance |
| Manual-only full-width slider (no timer) | Pattern 2 (disable `setInterval`) |
| Mixed-size content that should scroll | Pattern 1 (remove `scroll-snap-type` if needed) |

---

## Enforcement Level

**HIGH** — Agents must use one of these two patterns when building carousel or scroll components. Do not implement a third pattern from scratch.
